---

<PageShell
  title="Singapore Investor Visa 2026: GIP, EntrePass & Insurance Guide"
  description="Complete guide to Singapore's Global Investor Programme (GIP) and EntrePass. Investment requirements from SGD 10 million, tax benefits, world-class business environment, and healthcare coverage options."
  headline="Singapore Investor Visa: GIP, EntrePass & Insurance Guide"
  subheadline="Everything you need to know about Singapore's investor and entrepreneur visa options—Global Investor Programme for established investors, EntrePass for innovative startups, plus healthcare and insurance essentials."
  tocItems={tocItems}
  relatedLinks={relatedLinks}
  ctaButtonText="Compare Premium Insurance"
  ctaButtonHref="/go/cigna-global"
  heroImage="/images/countries/singapore-hero-bg.png"
>

  <!-- Trust Signals -->
  <div class="flex flex-wrap gap-4 mb-8 text-sm text-neutral-600">
    <span class="flex items-center gap-1">
      <svg class="w-4 h-4 text-green-600" fill="currentColor" viewBox="0 0 20 20"><path fill-rule="evenodd" d="M10 18a8 8 0 100-16 8 8 0 000 16zm3.707-9.293a1 1 0 00-1.414-1.414L9 10.586 7.707 9.293a1 1 0 00-1.414 1.414l2 2a1 1 0 001.414 0l4-4z" clip-rule="evenodd"></path></svg>
      Updated February 2026
    </span>
    <span class="flex items-center gap-1">
      <svg class="w-4 h-4 text-green-600" fill="currentColor" viewBox="0 0 20 20"><path fill-rule="evenodd" d="M10 18a8 8 0 100-16 8 8 0 000 16zm3.707-9.293a1 1 0 00-1.414-1.414L9 10.586 7.707 9.293a1 1 0 00-1.414 1.414l2 2a1 1 0 001.414 0l4-4z" clip-rule="evenodd"></path></svg>
      Official EDB/MOM Requirements
    </span>
    <span class="flex items-center gap-1">
      <svg class="w-4 h-4 text-green-600" fill="currentColor" viewBox="0 0 20 20"><path fill-rule="evenodd" d="M10 18a8 8 0 100-16 8 8 0 000 16zm3.707-9.293a1 1 0 00-1.414-1.414L9 10.586 7.707 9.293a1 1 0 00-1.414 1.414l2 2a1 1 0 001.414 0l4-4z" clip-rule="evenodd"></path></svg>
      0% Capital Gains Tax
    </span>
  </div>

  <!-- Section: Overview -->
  <section id="overview" class="scroll-mt-24 mb-12">
    <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-neutral-900 mb-4">Overview</h2>

    <p class="mb-4">
      Singapore is consistently ranked as the world's easiest place to do business, with a transparent legal system, zero capital gains tax, low corporate taxes (flat 17%), and access to the fastest-growing markets in Asia. For high-net-worth investors and innovative entrepreneurs, Singapore offers multiple pathways to residency—from the prestigious Global Investor Programme (GIP) that grants immediate permanent residence, to the EntrePass designed for startup founders.
    </p>

    <p class="mb-4">
      Unlike European golden visas focused on passive real estate investment, Singapore's investor programs emphasize active business involvement and economic contribution. The trade-off: higher investment thresholds but potentially greater returns in Asia's premier financial hub.
    </p>

    <div class="bg-primary-50 border border-primary-200 rounded-lg p-6 mb-6">
      <h3 class="font-semibold text-primary-900 mb-3">Key Facts: Singapore Investor Visas</h3>
      <ul class="space-y-2 text-primary-800">
        <li>• <strong>GIP Investment:</strong> SGD 10M (Option A), SGD 25M (Option B), or SGD 50M (Option C)</li>
        <li>• <strong>GIP Outcome:</strong> Permanent Residence from day one</li>
        <li>• <strong>EntrePass:</strong> No minimum investment, must have innovative/scalable business</li>
        <li>• <strong>PEP:</strong> For individuals earning SGD 270,000+/year</li>
        <li>• <strong>Corporate Tax:</strong> 17% flat rate (one of lowest globally)</li>
        <li>• <strong>Capital Gains Tax:</strong> 0%</li>
        <li>• <strong>Health Insurance:</strong> Not mandatory but essential (no public subsidy for foreigners)</li>
        <li>• <strong>Official Language:</strong> English (business and government)</li>
      </ul>
    </div>

    <h3 class="text-xl font-semibold text-neutral-900 mb-3">Why Choose Singapore?</h3>

    <div class="grid md:grid-cols-2 gap-6 mb-6">
      <div class="border border-green-200 bg-green-50 rounded-lg p-6">
        <h4 class="font-semibold text-green-900 mb-3">Advantages</h4>
        <ul class="space-y-2 text-green-800">
          <li>• 0% capital gains tax</li>
          <li>• 17% flat corporate tax rate</li>
          <li>• No inheritance tax</li>
          <li>• English as official business language</li>
          <li>• Rule of law and low corruption</li>
          <li>• Gateway to ASEAN and Asia-Pacific markets</li>
          <li>• World-class infrastructure and connectivity</li>
          <li>• Safe, clean, efficient city</li>
          <li>• GIP grants immediate permanent residence</li>
        </ul>
      </div>

      <div class="border border-amber-200 bg-amber-50 rounded-lg p-6">
        <h4 class="font-semibold text-amber-900 mb-3">Considerations</h4>
        <ul class="space-y-2 text-amber-800">
          <li>• Very high investment thresholds (GIP)</li>
          <li>• Stringent business track record requirements</li>
          <li>• High cost of living</li>
          <li>• Small city-state (limited geographic variety)</li>
          <li>• Healthcare expensive without insurance</li>
          <li>• Strict laws and regulations</li>
          <li>• Hot, humid tropical climate year-round</li>
          <li>• PR renewal requires maintaining business ties</li>
        </ul>
      </div>
    </div>

    <div class="bg-blue-50 border border-blue-200 rounded-lg p-4">
      <p class="text-blue-800">
        <strong>2023 GIP Changes:</strong> Singapore introduced Option C (Single Family Office) requiring SGD 50 million investment and at least SGD 200 million in assets under management. This reflects Singapore's growing status as a global wealth management hub, attracting ultra-high-net-worth families from around the world.
      </p>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- Section: Quick Decision Guide -->
  <section id="quick-decision" class="scroll-mt-24 mb-12">
    <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-neutral-900 mb-4">Quick Decision Guide</h2>

    <div class="grid md:grid-cols-2 gap-6 mb-6">
      <div class="bg-green-50 border border-green-200 rounded-lg p-6">
        <h3 class="font-semibold text-green-900 mb-3">Singapore Is Right For You If:</h3>
        <ul class="space-y-2 text-green-800">
          <li>You have an established business with 3+ years track record and SGD 200M+ annual revenue (GIP)</li>
          <li>You're building an innovative, scalable startup (EntrePass)</li>
          <li>You're a high-earning executive (SGD 270K+/year) seeking flexibility (PEP)</li>
          <li>You want access to Asian markets and capital</li>
          <li>You value tax efficiency (0% capital gains, 17% corporate)</li>
          <li>You prefer an English-speaking business environment</li>
          <li>You can afford premium healthcare costs</li>
          <li>Your family would thrive in a safe, modern city</li>
        </ul>
      </div>

      <div class="bg-amber-50 border border-amber-200 rounded-lg p-6">
        <h3 class="font-semibold text-amber-900 mb-3">Consider Other Options If:</h3>
        <ul class="space-y-2 text-amber-800">
          <li>You want passive investment without business involvement</li>
          <li>Your business revenue is below SGD 200M annually</li>
          <li>You prefer lower investment thresholds (Portugal: EUR 500K)</li>
          <li>You want European/Schengen access</li>
          <li>You prefer lower cost of living</li>
          <li>You need public healthcare subsidies</li>
          <li>You want a larger country with geographic variety</li>
          <li>Your business isn't technology or innovation-focused (EntrePass)</li>
        </ul>
      </div>
    </div>

    <h3 class="text-xl font-semibold text-neutral-900 mb-3">Which Singapore Visa Is Right for You?</h3>

    <ComparisonTable columns={visaComparisonColumns} rows={visaComparisonRows} />

    <div class="mt-6 space-y-4">
      <div class="border-l-4 border-green-500 pl-4">
        <h4 class="font-semibold text-neutral-900">Choose GIP if:</h4>
        <p class="text-neutral-600">You're an established business owner with significant wealth, want immediate permanent residence, and can invest SGD 10-50 million in Singapore's economy. Best for UHNW individuals seeking a base in Asia.</p>
      </div>

      <div class="border-l-4 border-blue-500 pl-4">
        <h4 class="font-semibold text-neutral-900">Choose EntrePass if:</h4>
        <p class="text-neutral-600">You're founding an innovative startup, have VC backing or strong IP, and want to build your company in Singapore. No minimum investment required, but your business must demonstrate scalability and innovation potential.</p>
      </div>

      <div class="border-l-4 border-purple-500 pl-4">
        <h4 class="font-semibold text-neutral-900">Choose PEP if:</h4>
        <p class="text-neutral-600">You're a high-earning executive (SGD 270,000+/year) wanting flexibility to work in Singapore without being tied to a specific employer. Valid for 3 years maximum, then requires conversion to other pass types.</p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- Section: Visa Requirements -->
  <section id="visa-requirements" class="scroll-mt-24 mb-12">
    <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-neutral-900 mb-4">Visa Requirements</h2>

    <p class="mb-4">
      Singapore offers three main pathways for investors and entrepreneurs. The Global Investor Programme (GIP) leads to permanent residence, while EntrePass and PEP provide work pass status with potential paths to PR over time.
    </p>

    <h3 class="text-xl font-semibold text-neutral-900 mb-3">Global Investor Programme (GIP)</h3>

    <p class="mb-4">
      The GIP is Singapore's premier investor immigration program, designed for experienced business owners and investors. It grants permanent residence immediately upon approval, with three investment options introduced in 2023.
    </p>

    <ComparisonTable columns={gipColumns} rows={gipRows} />

    <h4 class="text-lg font-semibold text-neutral-900 mt-6 mb-3">GIP Eligibility Requirements</h4>

    <div class="grid md:grid-cols-2 gap-6 mb-6">
      <div class="border border-neutral-200 rounded-lg p-6">
        <h5 class="font-semibold text-neutral-900 mb-3">Business Track Record</h5>
        <ul class="space-y-2 text-neutral-700">
          <li>• Minimum 3 years of audited financial statements</li>
          <li>• Annual revenue of at least SGD 200 million (most recent year)</li>
          <li>• Average revenue of SGD 200M over last 3 years</li>
          <li>• Must be a substantial shareholder in the company</li>
          <li>• Company must be in approved industries</li>
        </ul>
      </div>

      <div class="border border-neutral-200 rounded-lg p-6">
        <h5 class="font-semibold text-neutral-900 mb-3">Approved Industries</h5>
        <ul class="space-y-2 text-neutral-700">
          <li>• Aerospace Engineering</li>
          <li>• Alternative/Clean Energy</li>
          <li>• Automotive</li>
          <li>• Chemicals</li>
          <li>• Consumer Business</li>
          <li>• Electronics</li>
          <li>• Financial Services</li>
          <li>• Health & Life Sciences</li>
          <li>• ICT & Media</li>
          <li>• Logistics & Supply Chain</li>
        </ul>
      </div>
    </div>

    <h3 class="text-xl font-semibold text-neutral-900 mb-3">EntrePass (Entrepreneur Pass)</h3>

    <p class="mb-4">
      The EntrePass is designed for innovative entrepreneurs who want to start and operate a business in Singapore. Unlike GIP, there's no minimum investment amount—but your business must demonstrate innovation, scalability, and potential economic contribution.
    </p>

    <div class="grid md:grid-cols-2 gap-6 mb-6">
      <div class="border border-green-200 bg-green-50 rounded-lg p-6">
        <h4 class="font-semibold text-green-900 mb-3">EntrePass Eligibility</h4>
        <ul class="space-y-2 text-green-800">
          <li>• Must be registered (or plan to register) ACRA company</li>
          <li>• Must hold at least 30% shareholding</li>
          <li>• Business must be venture-backed, or</li>
          <li>• Hold significant IP, or</li>
          <li>• Have track record in established incubator</li>
          <li>• Company cannot be older than 6 months at application</li>
        </ul>
      </div>

      <div class="border border-blue-200 bg-blue-50 rounded-lg p-6">
        <h4 class="font-semibold text-blue-900 mb-3">Preferred Business Types</h4>
        <ul class="space-y-2 text-blue-800">
          <li>• Technology and software startups</li>
          <li>• Biotech and life sciences</li>
          <li>• Clean technology</li>
          <li>• Fintech</li>
          <li>• AI and machine learning</li>
          <li>• Deep tech</li>
          <li>• Businesses with strong IP portfolios</li>
          <li>• VC-backed ventures (Series A+ preferred)</li>
        </ul>
      </div>
    </div>

    <div class="bg-amber-50 border border-amber-200 rounded-lg p-4 mb-6">
      <p class="text-amber-800">
        <strong>EntrePass Renewals:</strong> Initial EntrePass is issued for 1 year. Renewal depends on meeting milestones: hiring local employees (at least 1 for first renewal, more for subsequent), minimum annual business spending (SGD 100,000+), and company revenue growth. Failure to meet benchmarks may result in non-renewal.
      </p>
    </div>

    <h3 class="text-xl font-semibold text-neutral-900 mb-3">Personalised Employment Pass (PEP)</h3>

    <p class="mb-4">
      The PEP is for high-earning professionals who want flexibility to work in Singapore without being tied to a specific employer. It's technically an employment pass variant rather than investor visa, but popular among executives and consultants.
    </p>

    <ul class="list-disc pl-6 space-y-2 mb-6">
      <li><strong>Income requirement:</strong> Fixed monthly salary of at least SGD 22,500 (SGD 270,000/year)</li>
      <li><strong>Duration:</strong> Maximum 3 years (non-renewable—must convert to other pass type)</li>
      <li><strong>Work flexibility:</strong> Can work for any employer in Singapore</li>
      <li><strong>Unemployment buffer:</strong> 6 months to find new employment between jobs</li>
      <li><strong>Not for:</strong> Sole proprietors, partners, company directors without salary</li>
    </ul>

    <div class="bg-blue-50 border border-blue-200 rounded-lg p-4">
      <p class="text-blue-800">
        <strong>Path to PR:</strong> EntrePass and PEP holders can apply for permanent residence after 2+ years of residency in Singapore. Approval depends on factors including business success, economic contribution, family ties, and integration. GIP grants PR immediately upon investment completion.
      </p>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- Section: Insurance Requirements -->
  <section id="insurance-requirements" class="scroll-mt-24 mb-12">
    <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-neutral-900 mb-4">Insurance Requirements</h2>

    <div class="bg-amber-50 border border-amber-200 rounded-lg p-6 mb-6">
      <h3 class="font-semibold text-amber-900 mb-2">Health Insurance is NOT Mandatory—But Essential</h3>
      <p class="text-amber-800">
        Unlike European investor visas, Singapore does not require health insurance for visa approval. However, foreigners do not receive subsidized healthcare rates—you pay full "foreigner" rates at public hospitals, which can be 3-5x higher than citizen rates. A single hospitalization can cost SGD 50,000-200,000. Comprehensive private insurance is strongly recommended.
      </p>
    </div>

    <p class="mb-4">
      Singapore's healthcare system is world-class—ranked 6th globally by WHO—but operates on a mixed public-private model. Citizens and permanent residents benefit from government subsidies and CPF Medisave. Foreigners on work passes have no access to these benefits and face full-cost pricing.
    </p>

    <ComparisonTable columns={insuranceColumns} rows={insuranceRows} />

    <h3 class="text-xl font-semibold text-neutral-900 mt-8 mb-3">Understanding Singapore Healthcare Costs</h3>

    <div class="grid md:grid-cols-2 gap-6 mb-6">
      <div class="border border-red-200 bg-red-50 rounded-lg p-6">
        <h4 class="font-semibold text-red-900 mb-3">Without Insurance (Foreigner Rates)</h4>
        <ul class="space-y-2 text-red-800">
          <li>• GP visit: SGD 50-150</li>
          <li>• Specialist consultation: SGD 150-400</li>
          <li>• Emergency room: SGD 500-2,000</li>
          <li>• Hospital stay (public): SGD 500-1,500/day</li>
          <li>• Hospital stay (private): SGD 1,000-5,000/day</li>
          <li>• Major surgery: SGD 30,000-150,000</li>
          <li>• ICU: SGD 3,000-10,000/day</li>
          <li>• Childbirth (private): SGD 15,000-30,000</li>
        </ul>
      </div>

      <div class="border border-green-200 bg-green-50 rounded-lg p-6">
        <h4 class="font-semibold text-green-900 mb-3">With Comprehensive Insurance</h4>
        <ul class="space-y-2 text-green-800">
          <li>• Monthly premium: SGD 300-1,000</li>
          <li>• Outpatient: Often included or small copay</li>
          <li>• Hospitalization: Fully covered to limits</li>
          <li>• Surgery: Covered after deductible</li>
          <li>• Specialists: Direct access, covered</li>
          <li>• Evacuation: Included in international plans</li>
          <li>• Pre-existing: Covered after waiting period</li>
          <li>• Global coverage: Use anywhere worldwide</li>
        </ul>
      </div>
    </div>

    <h3 class="text-xl font-semibold text-neutral-900 mb-3">International vs. Local Singapore Insurance</h3>

    <div class="grid md:grid-cols-2 gap-6 mb-6">
      <div class="border border-blue-200 bg-blue-50 rounded-lg p-6">
